= link_to "#top" do
  .back-to-top
    %h6.c-white.m-right-20 
      %span.m-right-5.h5-icon{"data-icon" => "i"}
      Back To Top
.strata-small
  .row.p-top-10
    .small-12.columns
      %h3.c-orange WINDOWS 10 ENTERPRISE APPLICATIONS  
  .row
    .small-we.large-9.columns
      %h5.c-blue What is a Windows 10 Application?
  .row
    .small-12.large-6.columns
      %p.p-top-5 A Windows 10 application is a customizable enterprise App that can integrate your company’s entire Line of Business (LOB) stack, social media, news, and business intelligence into a single, modern, touch-based experience for employees, channel partners, and/or customers.  The concept behind a Windows Enterprise App is simple—provide a single view of the heterogeneous Apps that exist in an organization today in an “single pane of glass” experience. In today’s diverse organization environments, it is not realistic or desirable to build a single, monolithic application.
    .small-12.large-6.columns
      = image_tag('https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/bcg-site-assets/Apportal/update/windows8.1laptop.png', style: "max-height: 260px;")
  .row
    .small-12.large-12.columns
      %p.p-top-5 
        Instead, organizations can use the flexibility of the Windows 10 OS to create a UI-based virtual integration.
        %span.c-orange With the help of a partner like Bloom, business users can initiate a new way to experience information in the enterprise that is extremely simple, intuitive and designed specifically for the modern UI. 
        And, because the App can deliver customized content based on the user’s role in the organization using Active Directory, the experience is all the better.
  .row
    .small-12.large-4.columns
      %h6.c-blue.p-top-10 Bloom was selected to partner with Microsoft to deliver the concept behind the “Patrol Car of the Future” with touch and voice activated tiles consolidating disparate data from across various police information sources.  We’re about to change the world! Join us!
    .small-12.large-8.columns
      = image_tag('https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/bcg-site-assets/Apportal/update/patrolcaroffuture.jpg', style: "max-height: 460px;")
  .row.p-top-10
    .small-12.large-12.columns
      %h5.c-blue.p-top-10 Why is a Windows 10 enterprise App a game changer?
